    "readme_description": "You are given a string `s`. We want to partition the string into as many parts as possible so that each letter appears in at most one part. For example, the string `\"ababcc\"` can be partitioned into `[\"abab\", \"cc\"]`, but partitions such as `[\"aba\", \"bcc\"]` or `[\"ab\", \"ab\", \"cc\"]` are invalid.\n\nNote that the partition is done so that after concatenating all the parts in order, the resultant string should be `s`.\n\nReturn _a list of integers representing the size of these parts_.",
